<item>
            <title>[HBASE-8660] [rest] support secure REST access</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-8660</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;REST interface is accessed over http, which is most likely done from outside of a HBase cluster, perhaps over internet.  It will be great if we can make it secure.  To be secure, we need to:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. authenticate the caller,&lt;br/&gt;
2. check authorization if needed,&lt;br/&gt;
3. make the connection secure (https)&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
